# =====================================================================
# This file is an example of the environment variables used by the
# backend if you were using a Node.js server (e.g., Netlify Functions).
#
# IMPORTANT: Since we are using Google Apps Script instead, you DO NOT
# need an actual .env file in this GitHub repository. 
# Google Apps Script handles authentication automatically for you.
# 
# However, if you ever migrate to a custom backend (like Node.js),
# these are the variables you would need to set in your server:
# =====================================================================

# (For Node.js Backend using Service Account)
# GOOGLE_CLIENT_EMAIL="your-service-account-email@gserviceaccount.com"
# GOOGLE_PRIVATE_KEY="-----BEGIN PRIVATE KEY-----\nYourKeyHere\n-----END PRIVATE KEY-----\n"

# (For Gmail SMTP sending)
# GMAIL_USER="your.email@gmail.com"
# GMAIL_APP_PASSWORD="your_16_character_app_password"

# CALENDAR_ID="primary" # or your specific calendar ID
